trans-unit.source: Represents a set of name/value pairs that identify an item of content.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref> class with a specified type name and namespace.
The type name and namespace for the <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref>.
The partType parameter is `null`.
The strings partType.
or partType.
(or both) are `null` or empty.
Creates a modifiable deep copy clone of this <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref>.
This <xref:System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart.Clone%2A> method creates modifiable copies of frozen <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> objects.
For convenience, this <xref:System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart.Clone%2A> method shadows the inherited version with a strongly typed implementation.
For more details, see <xref:System.Windows.Freezable.Clone%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.

The cloned <xref:System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart>'s <xref:System.Windows.Freezable.IsFrozen%2A> property will be `false` even if this source <xref:System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart>'s <xref:System.Windows.Freezable.IsFrozen%2A> property is `true.`

When copying dependency properties, <xref:System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart.Clone%2A> copies resource references and data bindings (although they might no longer resolve) but does not copy not animations or current animation values.
A modifiable deep copy clone of this <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref>.

Returns a value that indicates whether a given <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref> is identical to this <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref>.
The part to compare for equality.
`true` if the <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart.NameValuePairs"></xref> within both parts are identical; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the hash code for this part.
The hash code for this part.
Gets a collection of the name/value pairs that define this part.
The collection of the name/value pairs that define this <xref href="System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart"></xref>.
Gets the type name and namespace of the part.
The returned type name and namespace is originally defined in the parameter to the <xref:System.Windows.Annotations.ContentLocatorPart.%23ctor%2A> constructor.
The type name and namespace of the part.
